- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another likely category as the paper discusses the generation of lambda terms using a specific data structure, which is relevant to programming languages. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper uses a specific data structure (contexts) to generate lambda terms. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with the formalism of lambda calculus and its different classes of terms. 
- cs.TL (Type Theory) is a possible category as the paper mentions affine and linear lambda terms, which are related to type systems in programming languages.
